[?2004huser@9b9257e7c882:~/scheduler$ cat > FIX_SUMMARY.md << 'EOF'
[?2004l[?2004h> # Timezone Bug Fix Summary
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## Problem
[?2004l[?2004h> The scheduler app was sending meeting reminders at incorrect times, with a 1-hour offset for meetings between 2am-3am Berlin time (specifically during DST transitions).
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## Root Cause
[?2004l[?2004h> In `app.py`, the `convert_to_berlin()` function had a critical bug:
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ```python
[?2004l[?2004h> # BUGGY CODE (OLD):
[?2004l[?2004h> utc_dt = datetime.strptime(utc_time_str, '%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%S')
[?2004l[?2004h> berlin_dt = BERLIN_TZ.localize(utc_dt)  # WRONG: treats UTC as Berlin time!
[?2004l[?2004h> ```
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> The bug: `BERLIN_TZ.localize()` was being used on a naive datetime parsed from a UTC string. This incorrectly treated the UTC time as if it were already in Berlin timezone, rather than converting FROM UTC TO Berlin.
[?2004l[?2004h> 
[?2004l[?2004h> ## The Fix
[?2004l[?2004h> ```python
[?2004l[?2004h> # FIXED CODE (NEW):
